result.adr_address: 23 Elgin St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Holy Eats 好易食

reviews.text: Overall experience wasn’t pleasant. Extremely noisy! Booked for a table for three but seated at a table for two. Third guest sat on a cheap stool. Tables were extremely close to each other to maximize the number of guests in such a small area. Happy hour drinks were watered down. Soo much ice in the cocktails. Food was good. Service started out good. Not enough room on the table so we had to order in rounds. Time’s up and they start cleaning up before you’re done your food. Calculated the bill wrong. When we left there wasn’t anyone waiting for a table. What was all the rush for?!

Cool and hip spot. We had a great dinner experience. Loved the tattoo parlor feel with a holy yet sinful artistic twist decor. Generous food portions that were cooked perfectly and was delicious. Unfortunately I ate too much and was done for the rest of the night. Haha!
The food is too salty and not worth it. Good thing is the staff is very friendly. Still wouldn’t recommend.

Probably a 4 star if this was opened few years back, quite a number of similar Chinese fusion places around that might have done a better in terms of being creative with the food and drinks. Overpriced not so fusion food eg grilled chicken is basically soy sauce chicken you could get in any traditional Chinese restaurants for half the price. Overall an uninspiring effort but might still amaze some Soho first timers.
Good quality fusion food with a local twist. Some dishes are quite unique.
